raveling internationally. Naturally with our 113 year old house a few unexpected issues came up, and Lucio worked with us to resolve them. We love our new bathroom and would hire Lucio again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erika Gustafson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLhLLrejGefAC2zUEaXontjg2WrrEm_shgimZzLspeotWdgZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Lucio was called by a plumber as a contractor to head out to our house and dig a 5x5 hole to expose a leaking mainline pipe. Lucio charged us $3000 to dig a 3x3 hole not a 5x5 hole. He then informed the plumber that the entire mainline was galvanized piping and the entire mainline had to be replaced...100- 150 feet of it. The water meter is 40 feet from the front of my house... where he got 100 -150 feet is beyond me. Furthermore, he stated to dig up the mainline it would be $7500. I told him absolutely not, that 100-150 feet would be off of our property at that point and that would be absurd since our water meter is 40 feet from our home, plus $7500 for a few men to go dig? WHAT? We told him no. Then the next morning he text me stating his men are headed out there to do the $7500 job after I told him the night before NO..so when he text the next morning I told him absolutely not, and explained that my water meter is 40 feet from my front door, why would he dig 100-150 feet? That would be off my property. Well, his tone changed like \"oh\" he didnt realize that we have circular lots....he thought he could pull a fast one and that I would not know what length of pipe, if any, we would need. I had another plumber come out and fixed the leak for $1100, the mainline wasn't galvanized, only a transition piece was...house side was copper, then galvanized shut off transition to a normal standard mainline piping. Total scam and rip off, would never ever recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hiral","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2zFWwIKSS0MU7JqlEnmdGAV20JJPyHnztzSiCVti12zrfbMCd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This company and the owner seemed “FRAUD” to me. Lucio whose the owner of this company, fooled me with all his sweet talks and tried to show how professional he was but in reality all he did was broke the pipes while installing water heater, he didn’t repair it instead asked for more money to repair the damages he did. This isn’t professional behavior nor do verified companies do such thing like this one did. I hired him thinking that he is verified plumber but to be honest his was no where closer to a professional work nor was it up to the standard at all. He initially quoted me some lesser amount but later, he suddenly charged me way higher amount.\nAfter telling him that I am very disappointed for his shady work, he threatened me to pay the full amount.\nThis company looks shady to me and the guy too. He was very rude and extremely disrespectful.\nI would suggest that please do read the invoice throughly before signing and confirm all details and don’t trust him blindly.\nI lost trust in this company after all that happened with me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jon Weiss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6nPGrLjgpcP7kwVi7Wr0ubE8a6i0eM8WT6NFbySZUnvC3VNXM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hired to do a specific job for an approximate price.  He comes out claiming he can't do it without doing a couple of other things and the new estimate is four times more at $1,200.  Why agree to do work and change your mind on the jobsite?  I don't do business with scammers.  Now, he keeps threating me to to pay him a \"service fee\" of $165 for doing nothing.  This guy is not professional at all.  He is a scammer.  Avoid at all costs!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Annie wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsG26xleG4MN78f0jyDy7GFnnJf6_v-ZyLGOGvFKLcxtIz1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This company is a totally scam. You would pay $750 dollars to get the contractor to use a tool that you can rent from Home Depot with $50, and buy the tool with $500. Usually the same service just cost $250 from other companies. If you wanna get scammed by them, feel free to pick them. Btw the contractor name is Gabriel","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"On the road again CCS Trucking","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLxMasIYiwmwN4Vw6RPgOCDVWq0kVLK8wTxn0X2wOLIRqM1dw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Aloha and Mahalo to Lucio and his team for their experienced, courteous, professional quick and speedy service. I felt very comfortable with the entire process and will highly recommend and refer PCC to anyone and everyone.  Much Mahalo and Many Thanks Lucio and PCC\nWillie","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gabe Baro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJKi19KeLwHRT4f7WZe-rV6WQBSWTsgee01mDyM9OXoMBd_b4I=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I called these guys for an emergency with a customers drain and I’ve gotta say they’re the BEST. We probably talked for longer than it took him to diagnose and fix everything back to normal operation. Didn’t even leave a mess! I’ll call them during normal hours next time if I need a jetter or otherwise.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
