e ceramic tiles around the faucet! :-((  Then they mentioned that Ernesto is a skilled home repairman, positive and clear in his communications, and very reasonably priced.\n\nBut after I contacted Ernesto to schedule an appointment, I began to see even higher aspects of his skills:\n- He contacted me before our appointment, to make sure he was prepared for every possible need that might arise in his completing the repair...\n- He checked in with me on the way to his repair appointment, to let me know his exact arrival time...\n-He kept me posted on his progress at every stage of the repair--and even briefed me on what he'd be doing in the next stage as well...\n- And his actual tile replacement work was exceptional:  he was able to show me exactly which tiles must be replaced, and he did the replacement so skillfully!\n- All together, his restoration of the damaged tiles was really superb. You can't tell that any of the restored tiles weren't part of the original bath wall, because they replace the damaged tiles perfectly.\nIn short, Ernesto brilliantly accomplished the repair job and took care of my apprehensions about it, as well!  I can't recommend him highly enough...  All I can say is, give him a call, and I know his expertise and his kindness will amaze you too!\n...And one more thought:  since Ernesto's business card says his firm does all kinds of construction work, I wouldn't hesitate to call him for a major building project as well--because his work on my small reconstruction job was so careful and precise and beautiful!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pat Murray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgNK4IXoX1U6o0kT7VdniMBIOUazCTQcK1OvijNRzcY0X0xQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hired Ernesto to replace an outside railing system at my business property and I am very happy I did! He explained everything thoroughly kept his word on price and completion and did an excellent job! I could not be happier and I highly r