experience with Apollo Plumbing.  Nolan, Sergio, Kallista and Zac were absolutely amazing repairing a burst water line and replacing the mix of inferior crimp style pex and shark bite fittings that caused our water emergency.\nNolan visited our home first to examine the burst pipe and provide an estimate.  He arrived on time, assessed the situation quickly, and clearly explained the work that needed to be done.  A few days later, Zac, Callista and Sergio performed the repair and replacement work.  Everyone worked efficiently, all the while taking the time to explain what they were doing and what was going to happen next. They were understanding and patient every time we had a question. Kallista made time to also troubleshoot some problems across the street at my daughter’s house.  We are thankful for their hard work, attention to detail and dedication.\nOf course, my initial contact with Apollo Plumbing was with its office staff.  Every time I called, everyone I spoke with genuinely wanted me to receive the information and assistance I needed.\nApollo provided us with peace of mind at an extremely stressful and worrisome time. The quality of their work was exceptional, and they went above and beyond to make sure everything was done to perfection.  I highly recommend Apollo Plumbing.  They truly care about their customers and deliver outstanding results!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Ahl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLmEdK9HOiXuqZgLsY5C8XutwI4NgRUKcJDDYarKX7WFhchGA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nolan was the man!! Tenants called and said there was a water leak as the meter was showing a gallon loss every 16 seconds.  Nolan was dispatched out to our location within a couple hours and was able to identity the leak under the lawn about 10 yards from the house. Within about 1-2 hours of arrival this leak was fixed and we were able to get back to our day like we just took a long lunch break. Really appreciated!\n\n