":{"id":"113294288213362108052","name":"Allied Heating and Air Conditioning Solutions (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113294288213362108052"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"","city":"","postal_code":"","state":"","country":""},"about":[{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Robert Landlord","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKL_UkrpNe9TzoTbF2F6HL1Q2EBxxr0oOrLqHyuiX8IM2pfqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"James was able to fix my combi boiler when 3 other big companies in Seattle could not. Others quoted me ridiculous prices and I had already spent over $3000 on the unit without a fix, but James was able to accurately diagnose the issue in a single visit and fix it in the follow up, all while explaining to me how it worked.\n\nSuper responsive, would definitely recommend to all my friends!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa Battern","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDiQQXZrtsojMZBhabCkREVE8R27xYmMlsxtrTaILwIVRUowyyHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"James responded to our Facebook message immediately, on a Sunday evening. He took a considerable amount of time to discuss replacing our leaking water heater. We sent him text pictures which allowed him to propose options, and he presented a proposal that was in line with the other bid we received. He also provided an estimate for an option that was more energy efficient. I had researched our needs and was comfortable that all the information he shared was thorough and addressed all of our concerns.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cleber Lopes de Albuquerque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4mYZ4XaxqU6jhlAuKb5zMedpsJoTzjXdoSqEDyJB0-Eaz8-1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hired James from Allied Complete Furnace and AC to install an air conditioning unit, a gas line to a kitchen range, and add duct work to my home in Kenmore, WA. From the first contact over the phone to the completion of the service James was great to work with. He explained my options and had reasonable pricing. My first priority was to install a gas line to prepare for a new gas range that I purchased. James installed the new line using iron pipes instead of the less sturdy flexible pipes. When James came to install the air conditioning, he also found many issues with my current HVAC system, such as my furnace exhaust was never properly hooked up to the roof, the furnace was installed using taping, and some additional code violations. James fixed these code violations even though it wasn't part of his job. He also installed an air filtration system to my furnace, which is very helpful to maintain the house clean and will be nice during wild fire season, since it also filters smoke. James also found that our Nest thermostat was missing a power supply wire, which sometimes would cause the furnace to shutdown unexpectedly. James was also able to fix that. When it came to the air conditioning unit, he was very clear on my options and explained about a better value unit with a great warranty instead of trying to just sell the most expensive product. Our house has an addition that did not have the duct work. James quoted me a reasonable price and we decided to add ducts and vents to the addition. James and Roberto (carpenter) installed the ducts and a booster fan, to make sure we had good air flow and did an amazing job even matching our vents with the rest of the house. We have hardwood floors and they were very careful with our floors during the install.  After installing the system, James explained everything that was done, and how my system works. It’s now been over a month since the installation, and everything has been running smoothly.  I’m very happy that I chose Allied to do this work for us, and plan on using them in the future, and recommend to friends and family.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0NLaaF55Ji3IMdTIc_k14-CS6faH2wyJ55rAfxtFBfdn6JjI1a__hrLKLEuL6b6XE6p6GbcsAy_xk7ptvevbXsECQs1FRvYibw9VKOZZJ0P22HaELPU-WGu1EsxfSUNwVIKFU8Mw=k-no"],"When":"2021-5-13"},{"Name":"Ken Cross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvUYzgDxeQnMKbNNPg5HYlysjq7_FM0Wq7ufRgD6msFvnuXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Allied just finished a new heat pump system in our home. No more overheated summer nights! The work was beautiful, especially the custom sheet metal work. He completed the install in 3 days and that included an overnight leak check. The price is competitive, I'm very pleased and I think I have a new friend.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2PC1M1z3gkTs5cPU4qQn20xoCbKaGlKRuF-CaMCz9OhiATIxCQ4i5FRm9462gCrsSSsyMjrdZsfVfhltdOyf2xI7j0MdwfnZYjAaNNbPmB64CwuWy22b_QDF2MMy2Fl-kLXdNZ=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-30"},{"Name":"Eric Bosell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeFYGbbyh1wwfthFIrEok86cCuwMx0QcX7IJhBoRXZYBco4Ok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Holden Village recently worked with James Colver of Allied Heating and Air Conditioning, an outstanding HVAC contractor who exceeded expectations at every stage of a major water heating system upgrade. Beginning with the initial consultation, he carefully assessed our aging electric water heaters, listened to feedback from multiple stakeholders, and proposed a long-term solution tailored to our needs.\n\nHolden Village is a remote retreat center in the North Cascades Mountains, accessible only by ferry and bus. We generate our own hydroelectric power, operate our own water and septic systems, maintain historic buildings from the 1930s, and accommodate up to 300 guests. Every tool and part must be transported in by barge and truck—logistics most contractors never face.\n\nJames recommended a high-efficiency heat pump water heating system that is projected to reduce our hotel’s energy use by up to 90%, significantly easing the load on our hydro system and advancing our goal of becoming carbon neutral. He walked us through every detail with clarity and professionalism.\n\nDespite our unique infrastructure, James completed the installation seamlessly. He was prepared, skilled, and consistently respectful of our operations. More than delivering a product, he delivered insight, value, and care. We recommend him without reservation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Swat Cat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJzLXxDb9xh-kdrBkPYIAPzfGOVsLcB1DxPTy2QbqfGL38uSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I wanted to change the HVAC unit as it was old. I had also wanted to move away from gas furnace to a heat pump. I got a few quotes from companies but the reason I decided to go with James was because of how he took the time to explain  what this change means and all the questions I had. It was clear to me he knew what he was doing and the price was reasonable.\n\nI also want to mention that communication with James was seamless. He was prompt in responding and stuck to our schedule keeping me updated as needed. While working on setting up new heat pump, he gave recommendations on improving the existing wiring and also fixed other issues that he discovered. The work was completed on schedule.\n\nI was not used the new thermostat unit and was looking to see if I could change it to have the features the previous software had. He realized that I will be comfortable with the previous software and changed it the next day. Now it's perfect.\n\nOverall a 5 star service and I highly recommend James to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kirby Unti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpmMEO8WcFjI1Jhc4XW4zmBzqtgPKBQvlSAJILXHIGQSgY32IE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always look for three things in repair work honesty,competency  and fair pricing.  James delivers on all three.  He immediately diagnosed my water heater problem, had the part in hand the same day and had me up and running.  He is a man of utter integrity and my top choice for all my heating and ac needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ben Leader","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJz3yntCUP1fd4nGu5z5gDHQ_LlKiPIL2ui0PKc73StB5P6sA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"James is the best! I had him come out to service our furnace and tankless water heater this past summer. He clearly takes pride in his work, and even addressed a few small issues with the furnace that no previous contractor had bothered with at no extra cost.\n\nJust today I called him up because the ancient copper connector below our water heater sprang a leak. He offered to come by this week, but encouraged me to try replacing the connector myself and explained it was a common part and a quick job. One trip to the hardware store and a few minutes of work later and I'm back in business.\n\nAs a new homeowner trying to figure out when to DIY and when to call in a professional, knowing an honest, knowledgable, and friendly HVAC contractor is invaluable. I can wholeheartedly recommend Allied!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"05bfa496-737a-4953-9742-25a2e6b43831","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Uniplex+Construction,+LLC/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x549015a803423f63:0x41266d2b4d4fb86c!8m2!3d47.6801405!4d-122.1433881!16s%2Fg%2F11bbrkpr4z!19sChIJYz9CA6gVkFQRbLhPTSttJkE?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"4694559694328412268","title":"Uniplex Construction, LLC","categories":["Construction company"],"category":"Construction company","address":"14737 NE 87th St, Redmond, WA 98052","open_hours":{"Friday":["7:30 AM–4 PM"],"Monday":["7:30 AM–4 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["7:30 AM–4 PM"],"Tuesday":["7:30 AM–4 PM"],"Wednesday":["7:30 AM–4 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"http://www.uniplexconstruction.com/","phone":"(206) 323-4320","plus_code":"MVJ4+3J Redmond, Washington","review_count":18,"review_rating":4.8,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":1,"2":0,"3":0,"4":0,"5":17},"latitude":47.6801405,"longtitude":-122.1433881,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=9hZ0jMrjHN6pj2PbATzeLw\u0026cb_client=search.gws-prod.gps\u0026w=408\u0026h=240\u0026yaw=171.30957\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x549015a803423f63:0x41266d2b4d4fb86c","place_id":"ChIJYz9CA6gVkFQRbLhPTSttJkE","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=9hZ0jMrjHN6pj2PbATzeLw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=171.28027\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=9hZ0jMrjHN6pj2PbATzeLw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=171.28027\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"113284133430156622953","name":"Uniplex Construction, LLC (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113284133430156622953"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Willow - Rose Hill","street":"14737 NE 87th St","city":"Redmond","postal_code":"98052","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Dustin Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCQIqMvg5RFFiVexBoMPw3uixNe-NxlbCYNDrrIekB4zuWIg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uniplex has completed dozens of projects for me over the years totaling millions in contract value. Their attention to detail, quality of work, team's professionalism, and ability to navigate obstacles is outstanding and they are a great partner. They most recently completed a challenging exterior paint project on a 200+ unit 5-story podium apartment building, and the ownership/operating group is extremely pleased with the outcome. In construction, you get what you pay for, and I would highly recommend using Uniplex for any of your upcoming projects, big or small.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXpsH8a0x9jOcF0PQz7FDl5v1Yi7qSWIplp4OV8VCn5UvGRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a devastating house fire on November 20, 2024. Uniplex took care of us, managed complex insurance claims, frustrating mortgage inspections and restored our house to much better condition than before. Joe, Tracy and their entire team are experienced rockstars.  We have done 4 home remodels before and we could not be happier with their service, quality of workers, responsiveness, honesty and they completed the work on time and on budget! We HIGHLY recommend Uniplex.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don Hall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ZBH8vAvcSN7QoP5oMZjRmacneY5517YbOEWkLY5t3mtud77Diw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uniplex recently completed a big home renovation project for us (kitchen remodel, primary bath remodel, new flooring, and updates to secondary bathrooms) and, now that it is all done, we are absolutely loving the end results.\n\nOver a 9-month process from the first meeting to the completion of the project, we were extremely pleased with the quality of Uniplex's work as well as their attention to detail, hands-on problem-solving, and excellent communication and project management.\n\nDuring the initial visit and proposal phase, we were very impressed with the questions they asked and how they enlisted their sub-contractors into the process to get tighter, more informed estimates. Joe Schwab, the Uniplex CEO, understood our objectives and overall design vision. He stayed involved through the project, kept us in the loop, and treated us as partners with a shared goal. If there were material delays or other impacts to the schedule, the Uniplex team found ways to stay on track. They actually ended up finishing the project ahead of schedule, so we could enjoy our 'new' home with family for the holidays.\n\nThe entire Uniplex team was talented, friendly, and courteous. It was clear they really cared about the quality of their work and had a ton of relevant experience. They also took extra effort to clean up the job site every day since we were living in the house during construction.\n\nWe feel really fortunate to have worked with Uniplex and would highly recommend them.\n\nUPDATE MAY 2024: We put our house on the market in April and it was under contract within one week at 12% over the asking price. We attribute a lot of the price premium we received to the very high quality work that Uniplex did for us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ellie Alley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZ2NBrT2pekazRU8Y1WBqpJab845SWIXdJiiWdrFJZN3wFlQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I worked with Uniplex to remodel our 1935 Seattle home -- including a total gut renovation of our kitchen, bathroom, bedroom, and multiple other cosmetic changes. In addition to the scope of the project itself, we had an additional layer of complexity given we needed the work completed within no more than 3 months due to a new baby joining the family shortly thereafter.\n\nOf the three construction firms we received bids from, Uniplex was the only company willing to commit to and stand by a firm timeline without sacrificing scope or quality. Their bid was extremely detailed -- reducing any uncertainty in what was expected and allowing the project to progress seamlessly -- and the price was on par with the other bids received.\n\nThe supervisor assigned to our project was one of the nicest people I've met in the construction industry. He went above and beyond to ensure the house was clean at the end of each work day (since we were living in it while construction was underway), brought donuts for our daughter enjoy in the morning, and texted whenever there were changes or updates worth noting.\n\nUniplex took what could have been an incredibly stressful home renovation and gave us the confidence that we would end up with a home perfect for our growing family -- which we did. I can't recommend them enough!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Moore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0Qu9tb1b_3JwHzTfkzVm24ghognUVh-A6-6DN4W5o8SUBgbE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uniplex repaired extensive damage to our home resulting from a broken ice maker supply line in our kitchen. The work quality was excellent and our home looks great again. The project management team worked tirelessly to juggle all the subcontractors and suppliers to keep the project on schedule. They coordinated with our insurance company and brought in other professionals as needed to ensure a well executed project. We will definitely be using Uniplex in the future as well as referring them to our friends and family.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amanda Strome","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDIXE9B0IkWAUn4NPoiBR-_Dx9zD89Fh8GtY1lZ7dcvqUaIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Where to begin? The people who make up Uniplex are amazing! They help our hand through the entire process of restoring our house after a sewage flood. Their employees are so professional, knowledgeable, and above most friendly! They are fair and honest people. Their work is incredible and they work in a very timely manner! I am already trying to come up with an excuse to have them back to our house because I grew so close to these people! Look no further- it just doesn’t get any better than this group of people! They do it all and they do everything so well!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jane smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkyUOsbBAQHO6h6cpk_YwzxNJIyDkMuG_0OdpkaFNQBJTHCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"this company works with scammers they send checks from the rotsry club in usps priority mail mail envelopes to elderly women fit them to deposit in their accounts and then 2 weeks later pull the checks back and the elderly woman is stuck owing the money the scammer borrowed and thr 25676 i know i have the envelope and the check in my possession right now don’t trust a company that will cheat elderly woman it could be your mom next","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Lohman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJY5zktfksK2w85XD4YRVqlURLoKxK520KcU8VdFDkbHOcKCA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Uniplex repaired significant damage to our home resulting from a broken water supply line while we were on vacation. The work quality was excellent and our home looks great again. They coordinated with our insurance company and brought in other professionals as needed to ensure a properly executed project.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails"