rtificate of warranty, that we didn't get it.  Yet, our certified installer of the pump follow steps in the mfg APP, and it is listed in their Portal site accessed by the dealer(Correct Equipment Inc).\n\nComplaint as Public Record: Yes\nDisclosure Notices: Yes\n\neONE does not stand behind their product, neither did Correct Equipment Inc.  Essentially had to pay twice for the solution, and still have no warranty!  Beware.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0P9KMLyloBuCdZefLvs5qyNj-47n7_BK9AKm_N6XeTXKI2h8asIokwy3p-vqWkYiizFbbu8EMclJQfY0LXenfS8WAEnrfuDG5pySZKFRteA4Z5pOpMsL7qpXZdfddL_6OXNsrXGg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2qqlZ3lz1cdACq70ow6o8fpAlVmiFE-NnMtonY_Wkrr3Ve5Sw7YbL_fWivd6Nu2OHTgbOsGFi_5IyL06qwui9SbAWX1U1SyJqt7_zMF7rmyYvdZ2aG8JjEUI5Ml9jYEoMcoulb=k-no"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Luis da Silva Torres","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwNWUzgp_rw-Bw1YD7SUacimiOPC4RDPRxa3y-vo4D0TbC8eY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I called Correct Equipment Inc. and spoke with a woman named Lauren. When I asked, “Can you hear me?” she just replied, “No, I can’t hear you  bye,” and hung up immediately. Even if there was a connection issue, that’s not how you handle a customer call. A little patience or professionalism would’ve gone a long way. Very disappointing experience and not what I’d expect from a company representing itself to the public.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vanny Thavixay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKqdhvozp7ooa5ZC01ttcc0nzJ4DtZhPR3zUlvbH_nCL9chZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Correct equipment was quick and responsive when i called about my grinder pump alarm going off. They sent someone as soon as possible the same day. It was a great experience working with Duane. He was knowledgeable, friendly and fast. He answered all of our questions and left us with no concerns. I highly recommend this company.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKc8Gebpl--ITMILl91wYxFiBWDKTrV1dIyCDU3xYCfSP7XdAk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always use this company if your E-One Grinder Pump has an issue. I went to another company first (Beacon Plumbing) and they quoted me $11,500 to replace the pump after doing no testing to diagnose a problem. Correct Equipment came out in one day and fixed the pump (not replace) and got it back up for $1038. The two guys that helped were Santos and Vince and they were great. They kept me informed about what they had to do and how everything worked. They were very professional and trustworthy.  It was a great experience working with this company. I gave all my neighbors their card.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alice Finseth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLOmB8f7b8U-FJHz-y1PJudzPrYoGGcS3Hlt8MSdPiP6p6wDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you have an E-One Grinder Pump, Correct Equipment is the only company you need to call. We used a different company first (Flohawks) and they did a terrible job, took our pump to their workshop, left us without a pump for 10 days, not giving us updates and wanting to charge us for things that they weren't even sure they knew how to fix and didn't even have the parts. I asked for our pump to be returned and called Correct Equipment. Vince came to our house and repaired everything on-site in just a couple hours and clearly knew what he was doing. He's professional, trustworthy, he explained to me everything he was doing, and he clearly cares about his customers. He worked efficiently and the bill at the end wasn't nearly as expensive as the other company wanted to charge us for. This is a no-brainer, I would recommend this company to anyone who needs their E-one fixed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Becky Lovall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLi1kmT7VVpv_xI99mc4HRqnwNhwBBxc6ODHejfVjbszW0eow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Duane was our technician and did a fantastic job. We had another company come out and fix a different sewer issue. That company gave us the runaround and ended up spending $1600.00 before they told us that our grinder pump wasn’t working properly, and that they could not work on our type of grinder pump. What the first company didn’t tell me was that they didn’t open the grinder pump valve and had kept the grinder pump on, essentially over working the grinder pump engine. Duane was able to quickly figure the type the issue and replaced some parts to allow my overworked grinder pump to work properly again! Thank you Duane for coming out on a Saturday and ending our 10 day sewer debacle!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Josh Huhndorf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHhBp6L1Hw7LxClNHgp-54sEdu_7F7hBhTvfJc9rujov-zHYZk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Phenomenal service! Called and got a quote and they sent an amazing serviceman (Jackson) out the next day! He definitely went the extra mile for us. Diagnosed and replaced our old E1 pump the same day! Our home is back to normal again!! Thank you!!!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
